to the editor re socialism triumphs on the gridiron editorial dec 30 you rightly praise the national football league 's policy of parity as opposed to major league baseball 's where the same handful of teams dominate every year but as a preface to this you state that fidel castro is partial to the wrong american sport hardly if anything mr castro most likely looks upon george steinbrenner ted turner and company as half hearted deviationists when alex rodriguez wanted to flee his billionaire owners in seattle all he had to do was to hire an agent and sit back and wait for the offers to start pouring in a rather easier process than orlando hernandez had to go through when he wanted to leave one of mr castro 's little cartel of teams andy moursund kensington md dec 30 2000

